healthy kitchen 101 and 102 events at stanford healthy kitchen 101 and 102 facebook twitter email print add to calendar as a society we seem to have lost our cooking skills long working hours and endless responsibilities make convenient fast foods a tempting option which can have consequences to our health does the thought of cooking seem overwhelming to you if so come to these two classes to learn healthy cooking basics healthy kitchen 101 healthy kitchen essentials this session will go over equipment and pantry items that all kitchens big or small should have to make easy nutritional meals a healthy meal demonstration will be included healthy kitchen 102 hands on meal making in this session you will participate in making a healthy low cost and plant based recipe using the learned kitchen essentials from session 1 participants will be able to taste their culinary creation and take the recipe home along with a handout of other easy healthy recipes created by your instructors kitchen 101 required to take kitchen 102 instructors patricia o keefe girbal rd lauren stinson bs rosalyne tu ms rd are bewell wellness advisors and nutritionists from speaking with many bewell participants they were inspired to create this class to make healthy eating easier and less costly when tuesday october 18 2011 12 00 pm approximate duration of 1.0 hour s where arrillaga family dining commons map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public members tags class health wellness sponsor health improvement program contact 650 721 6003 ausserer stanford edu admission register for these two classes at hip stanford edu healthy kitchen 101 class fee $50 class code hkit 01 stap ea funds yes healthy kitchen 102 class fee $10 class code hkit 02 stap ea funds no permalink http events stanford edu events 290 29017 more info last modified october 11 2011
